      <script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"ScholarlyArticle","abstract":"Commercial household detergents are diverse group of chemical that is best known for their wide used in laundry industries and household cleaning product. After use, residuals (Surfactant) detergents are discharge into sewage system directly or indirectly into the surface water and most of them end up dispersed into the different environment compartment of soil and water.”Water is facing lots of problems due to domestic waste. These toxic effects of surfactant damaging biodiversity of aquatic environment. Most of aquatic microorganism develops a bio-mechanism for degradation of harmful heavy metals discharge in water at high level. As we know that aquatic environment specially water “fungi” have excellent potential for metal accumulation, particularly genera of Rhizopus, Aspergillus, Streptoverticillum, Sacchromyctes. In general most of commercial household (Surfactants) detergents are biodegradable and amount of it can be commerciallyreduced by secondary treatment of Municipal sewage waste water plants. These discharge waste water pollutants with massive quantities especially surfactant could be a serious threat to aquatic ecosystem. Future studies of Commercial Surfactant toxicities and biodegradation are necessary to withdraw high toxic and non-biodegradableheavy metal for commercial use as a result makes an eco-friendly environment. Keywords: Biodegradation, Surfactant Toxicity, Heavy metals, Municipal sewage waste.","author":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Person","name":"Dr Amiy Chaturvedi","url":"https://independent.academia.edu/DrAmiyChaturvedi","image":"https://0.academia-photos.com/4924081/6679153/7546286/s200_dr_amiy.chaturvedi.jpg","sameAs":[]}],"contributor":[],"dateCreated":"2015-01-12","dateModified":"2015-01-12","headline":"Effect of Household detergents (Surfactants)Degraded through aquatic fungi","image":"https://attachments.academia-assets.com/36238406/thumbnails/1.jpg","inLanguage":"en","keywords":["Metagenomics, Molecular Microbiology (PCR, Sanger-Sequencing, NGS), Cellular and Molecular Biology, Genomics, Cell Dynamics, etc"],"publisher":{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Organization","name":null},"sourceOrganization":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"EducationalOrganization","name":null}],"thumbnailUrl":"https://attachments.academia-assets.com/36238406/thumbnails/1.jpg","url":"https://www.academia.edu/10123107/Effect_of_Household_detergents_Surfactants_Degraded_through_aquatic_fungi"}</script><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","about":{"@type":"ScholarlyArticle","name":"Effect of Household detergents (Surfactants)Degraded through aquatic fungi","url":"https://www.academia.edu/10123107/Effect_of_Household_detergents_Surfactants_Degraded_through_aquatic_fungi"},"mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What fungi species were effective in degrading household detergents?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The study identified 58 fungal species, predominantly 50 anamorphic fungi, with significant potential for detergent degradation."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How were fungal populations affected by detergent concentrations?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Increasing detergent concentrations negatively impacted the biomass of the dominant fungal species identified in wastewater."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What methodology was used to assess detergent degradation by fungi?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Detergent degradation was evaluated through optical density measurements before and after fungal inoculation in wastewater samples."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What are the implications of fungi on domestic wastewater treatment?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Fungi can play a crucial role in bioremediation, potentially removing harmful surfactants from domestic wastewater."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do synthetic detergents impact aquatic ecosystems according to this study?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Synthetic detergents have been found to significantly disrupt aquatic ecosystems, affecting microbial populations essential for nutrient cycling."}}]}</script><link rel="stylesheet" href="//a.academia-assets.com/assets/design_system/default_tokens/rebrand-89afffb91e093c5385bc943212566acb82d8da08820977c439fbb6656b3d411c.css" media="all" /><link rel="stylesheet" href="//a.academia-assets.com/assets/single_work_page/loswp_redesigns/ungated_variant-396bbd21fb1213413912bc4f8905c077ab09f4e6f899c0094ab7368fc7fa8fa0.css" media="all" /><link rel="stylesheet" href="//a.academia-assets.com/assets/design_system/heading-95367dc03b794f6737f30123738a886cf53b7a65cdef98a922a98591d60063e3.css" media="all" /><link rel="stylesheet" href="//a.academia-assets.com/assets/design_system/body-c50f5ab98832f511df8842993148351135752147645352dc0b07c369bcb29ab7.css" media="all" /><link rel="stylesheet" href="//a.academia-assets.com/assets/design_system/button-4d6745f84a0a0d8316c46d93a0bc87b9c96d3bce729ca2b864b618764cddd832.css" media="all" /><link rel="stylesheet" href="//a.academia-assets.com/assets/design_system/text_button-d1941ab08e91e29ee143084c4749da4aaffa350a2ac6eec2306b1d7a352d911a.css" media="all" /><link rel="stylesheet" href="//a.academia-assets.com/assets/single_work_page/accordion-db99f5a0fda3c12c056b88b46879e95c504112cd02807f4c526634dfb6529288.css" media="all" /><link rel="stylesheet" href="//a.academia-assets.com/assets/single_work_page/ai_label-ce27a6e5844b0ce31dcb42cc62f5f415c06ca204b3d13705c41e2471d0fb65fd.css" media="all" /><link rel="stylesheet" href="//a.academia-assets.com/assets/single_work_page/ordered_list-9123030494f589694fc98dd7b689a70398eb527516b541b1c648dce5ab690c12.css" media="all" /><link as="fetch" crossorigin="anonymous" href="https://attachments.academia-assets.com/36238406/1.html" rel="preload" /><link 