Abstract" id="abstract"><summary><h2 class="ds2-5-heading-sans-serif-md accordion-section__title">Abstract</h2></summary><div class="safe-abstract--container"><div class="safe-abstract--body"><style>.truncate-component {
  position: relative;

  overflow: hidden;
  display: -webkit-box;
  line-clamp: 16;
  -webkit-line-clamp: 16;
  -webkit-box-orient: vertical;
}

.toggle-truncation-button {
  display: none;
  position: absolute;
  bottom: 0;
  right: 0;
}</style><div class="truncate-component js-truncate-component--abstract"><p class="ds2-5-body-md">Commercial household detergents are diverse group of chemical that is best known for their wide used in laundry industries
and household cleaning product. After use, residuals (Surfactant) detergents are discharge into sewage system directly or
indirectly into the surface water and most of them end up dispersed into the different environment compartment of soil and
water.”Water is facing lots of problems due to domestic waste. These toxic effects of surfactant damaging biodiversity of
aquatic environment. Most of aquatic microorganism develops a bio-mechanism for degradation of harmful heavy metals
discharge in water at high level. As we know that aquatic environment specially water “fungi” have excellent potential for
metal accumulation, particularly genera of Rhizopus, Aspergillus, Streptoverticillum, Sacchromyctes. In general most of
commercial household (Surfactants) detergents are biodegradable and amount of it can be commerciallyreduced by
secondary treatment of Municipal sewage waste water plants. These discharge waste water pollutants with massive
quantities especially surfactant could be a serious threat to aquatic ecosystem. Future studies of Commercial Surfactant
toxicities and biodegradation are necessary to withdraw high toxic and non-biodegradableheavy metal for commercial use as
a result makes an eco-friendly environment.
Keywords: Biodegradation, Surfactant Toxicity, Heavy metals, Municipal sewage waste.</p><div class="toggle-truncation-button js-toggle-truncation-button--abstract"><button class="safe-abstract--toggle-truncation-button"><span>... </span><span class="safe-abstract--toggle-truncation-button-text">Read more</span></button></div></div></div></div></details><details class="accordion js-loswp-accordion" data-section-name="Key takeaways" id="key-takeaways"><summary><h2 class="ds2-5-heading-sans-serif-md accordion-section__title">Key takeaways</h2><div class="ai-label ai-label--ungated"><img alt="sparkles" src="//a.academia-assets.com/images/icons/sparkle.svg" width="16" height="16" /><p class="ds2-5-body-xs">AI generated</p></div></summary><div class="ds-key-takeaways--container"><div class="key-takeaways--content"><ol class="ordered-list key-takeaways--list"><li class="ordered-list--item ds2-5-body-md">Commercial household detergents contribute significantly to water pollution, threatening aquatic biodiversity.</li><li class="ordered-list--item ds2-5-body-md">Aquatic fungi demonstrate potential for biodegradation of toxic surfactants and heavy metals in wastewater.</li><li class="ordered-list--item ds2-5-body-md">Over 4.2 million tons of detergent were used annually in Western Europe a decade ago.</li><li class="ordered-list--item ds2-5-body-md">Fungi isolated from wastewater showed varied degradation rates of surfactants, with some achieving over 90% degradation.</li><li class="ordered-list--item ds2-5-body-md">Future studies must focus on eco-friendly alternatives and enhancing wastewater treatment technologies.</li></ol><script type="application/json" id="js-react-on-rails-context">{"componentRegistryTimeout":5000,"railsEnv":"production","inMailer":false,"i18nLocale":"en","i18nDefaultLocale":"en","rorVersion":"16.1.2","rorPro":true,"rorProVersion":"3.3.1","href":"https://www.academia.edu/10123107/Effect_of_Household_detergents_Surfactants_Degraded_through_aquatic_fungi","location":"/10123107/Effect_of_Household_detergents_Surfactants_Degraded_through_aquatic_fungi","scheme":"https","host":"www.academia.edu","port":null,"pathname":"/10123107/Effect_of_Household_detergents_Surfactants_Degraded_through_aquatic_fungi","search":null,"httpAcceptLanguage":null,"autoProps":{},"serverSide":false}</script>
<div id="FeatureFeedback-react-component-53646e19-fda0-448d-8be9-61844c2d2a10"></div>
<script type="application/json" class="js-react-on-rails-component" id="js-react-on-rails-component-FeatureFeedback-react-component-53646e19-fda0-448d-8be9-61844c2d2a10" data-component-name="FeatureFeedback" data-dom-id="FeatureFeedback-react-component-53646e19-fda0-448d-8be9-61844c2d2a10">{"featureName":"key_takeaways"}</script></div></div></details><details class="accordion js-loswp-accordion" data-section-name="FAQ&#39;s" id="faq"><summary><h2 class="ds2-5-heading-sans-serif-md accordion-section__title">FAQ&#39;s</h2><div class="ai-label ai-label--ungated"><img alt="sparkles" src="//a.academia-assets.com/images/icons/sparkle.svg" width="16" height="16" /><p class="ds2-5-body-xs">AI generated</p></div></summary><div class="work-faq--container"><div class="work-faq--list"><details class="work-faq--item" data-faq-number="1"><summary class="work-faq--question js-faq-question"><span class="work-faq--question-text" data-question="What fungi species were effective in degrading household detergents?">What fungi species were effective in degrading household detergents?</span><span class="material-symbols-outlined work-faq--icon" style="font-size: 18px" translate="no">add</span></summary><div class="work-faq--answer"><p class="ds2-5-body-md">The study identified 58 fungal species, predominantly 50 anamorphic fungi, with significant potential for detergent degradation.</p></div></details><details class="work-faq--item" data-faq-number="2"><summary class="work-faq--question js-faq-question"><span class="work-faq--question-text" data-question="How were fungal populations affected by detergent concentrations?">How were fungal populations affected by detergent concentrations?</span><span class="material-symbols-outlined work-faq--icon" style="font-size: 18px" translate="no">add</span></summary><div class="work-faq--answer"><p class="ds2-5-body-md">Increasing detergent concentrations negatively impacted the biomass of the dominant fungal species identified in wastewater.</p></div></details><details class="work-faq--item" data-faq-number="3"><summary class="work-faq--question js-faq-question"><span class="work-faq--question-text" data-question="What methodology was used to assess detergent degradation by fungi?">What methodology was used to assess detergent degradation by fungi?</span><span class="material-symbols-outlined work-faq--icon" style="font-size: 18px" translate="no">add</span></summary><div class="work-faq--answer"><p class="ds2-5-body-md">Detergent degradation was evaluated through optical density measurements before and after fungal inoculation in wastewater samples.</p></div></details><details class="work-faq--item" data-faq-number="4"><summary class="work-faq--question js-faq-question"><span class="work-faq--question-text" data-question="What are the implications of fungi on domestic wastewater treatment?">What are the implications of fungi on domestic wastewater treatment?</span><span class="material-symbols-outlined work-faq--icon" style="font-size: 18px" translate="no">add</span></summary><div class="work-faq--answer"><p class="ds2-5-body-md">Fungi can play a crucial role in bioremediation, potentially removing harmful surfactants from domestic wastewater.</p></div></details><details class="work-faq--item" data-faq-number="5"><summary class="work-faq--question js-faq-question"><span class="work-faq--question-text" data-question="How do synthetic detergents impact aquatic ecosystems according to this study?">How do synthetic detergents impact aquatic ecosystems according to this study?</span><span class="material-symbols-outlined work-faq--icon" style="font-size: 18px" translate="no">add</span></summary><div class="work-faq--answer"><p class="ds2-5-body-md">Synthetic detergents have been found to significantly disrupt aquatic ecosystems, affecting microbial populations essential for nutrient cycling.</p></div></details></div></div><script>document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
  function getCookie(name) {
    const value = `; ${document.cookie}`;
    const parts = value.split(`; ${name}=`);
    if (parts.length === 2) return parts.pop().split(';').shift();
